1488
01:19:48,290 --> 01:19:52,505
All right, now the expected
value of R is easy.

1489
01:19:55,230 --> 01:19:57,270
It's just by linearity
of expectation,

1490
01:19:57,270 --> 01:20:00,590
expected value of
R1 and so forth

1491
01:20:00,590 --> 01:20:01,890
plus the expected value of Rn.

1492
01:20:05,310 --> 01:20:10,150
The expected value of an
indicator random variable

1493
01:20:10,150 --> 01:20:13,350
is just the probability
that it's 1.

1494
01:20:13,350 --> 01:20:15,040
Right it's 1 times
the probability,

1495
01:20:15,040 --> 01:20:17,484
it's 0 times the
probability of 0.

1496
01:20:17,484 --> 01:20:19,150
That's just the
probability that it's 1.

1497
01:20:28,650 --> 01:20:31,680
What's the probability that the
first man gets the right hat

1498
01:20:31,680 --> 01:20:34,400
back?

1499
01:20:34,400 --> 01:20:35,080
1 over n.

1500
01:20:35,080 --> 01:20:35,730
There's n hats.

1501
01:20:35,730 --> 01:20:38,820
He gets a random one.

